cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with supervised feature learning using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for medical image analysis, specifically for assessing emphysema extent in chest CT scans. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of visual similarity triplets to learn a low dimensional embedding using CNNs, which is a machine learning (cs.LG) technique. The use of similarity triplets also involves assessing patterns and reducing rater variability, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with medical images, which could also fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
